      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Expose verified ClawHub source in skill verify output",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nRefs #92077. Follow-up to #93506.\n\nThis PR exposes the trusted ClawHub source provenance that #93506 started consuming in one more user-visible surface:\n\n- Adds `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl` to `openclaw skills verify` JSON output when ClawHub verification returns server-resolved GitHub provenance.\n- Reuses the same trust-boundary helper for install persistence and verify output, so unsupported provenance shapes remain untrusted.\n- Builds the promoted source URL from server-resolved `repo` + `commit` + optional `path`, producing a commit-pinned GitHub URL instead of trusting the raw `provenance.url` field, which can point at a mutable ref such as `main`.\n- Documents the new verify JSON field in the skills CLI docs.\n\nThis does not read or promote self-attested `SKILL.md` metadata from #92860. It also does not replace #93314, which is still the readback half for provenance already written to local `.clawhub/origin.json`.\n\n## Behavior addressed\n\nUsers and tooling consuming `openclaw skills verify` JSON can now find the verified source URL under the OpenClaw-owned metadata envelope without guessing whether raw ClawHub `provenance.url` is immutable or trusted.\n\nUnavailable provenance or any non-`server-resolved-github-import` provenance stays only in the raw verification envelope and is not promoted as `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: `openclaw skills verify` JSON now promotes only server-resolved ClawHub GitHub provenance into a commit-pinned `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl`.\n\nConflict/merge proof after prepare:\n\n- Rebased the narrow PR stack onto `origin/main` at `f50812dd56`.\n- `git merge-tree $(git merge-base HEAD origin/main) origin/main HEAD` reports a clean merged result with no conflict records.\n- Current PR diff is scoped to ClawHub verify output implementation, focused tests, and docs only: `docs/cli/skills.md`, `src/cli/skills-cli.ts`, `src/cli/skills-cli.verify.test.ts`, `src/cli/skills-cli.commands.test.ts`, `src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.ts`, and `src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts`.\n- Local signature verification with the configured SSH signing public key reports all prepared commits as good signatures: `ad66207604 G`, `8a06d22861 G`, and `c1059e3b9b G`.\n\nExact focused checks run after rebasing onto current `main`:\n\n```sh\nPNPM_CONFIG_MODULES_DIR=../../node_modules node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.cli.config.ts src/cli/skills-cli.verify.test.ts src/cli/skills-cli.commands.test.ts\nPNPM_CONFIG_MODULES_DIR=../../node_modules node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.unit-src.config.ts src/skills/lifecycle/clawhub.test.ts\nnode --import tsx scripts/generate-prompt-snapshots.ts --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\nCLI verify/command tests: 2 files passed, 52 tests passed\nClawHub lifecycle tests: 1 file passed, 42 tests passed\nPrompt snapshots: current (7 files) after regenerating the 6 drifted Codex happy-path snapshots reported by CI\n```\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- A verification response with `provenance.source: \"server-resolved-github-import\"`, `repo: \"openclaw/skills\"`, `commit: \"def456\"`, and `path: \"agentreceipt\"` produces `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl: \"https://github.com/openclaw/skills/tree/def456/agentreceipt\"`.\n- A verification response with unavailable or self-declared provenance does not produce `openclaw.verifiedSourceUrl`.\n- Install persistence and verify output continue sharing the same helper, so only server-resolved provenance is promoted.\n\nLive-sample limitation: there is still no live positive production ClawHub provenance sample available for this contract. The PR body records that limitation explicitly, and the focused CLI/lifecycle tests exercise the server-resolved provenance envelope that ClawHub returns for this feature.\n\n\n",
        "branch": "feature/issue-92077-verified-source-verify-output",
